Way better than we expected!  We were looking for a place that had more than just bagels/quick bites and found this place. Seated within 2min at 10am on a Tuesday, ordered and waited no longer than 5min for both our deluxe coffee drinks and about 8min for the food. We were surprised because we were watching them make food within 1 min of sitting down and found out that it was actually OUR food, which was surprising given how busy they were. Which leads me to the food...the food was AMAZING. The Martin breakfast sandwich was delicious and the French toast was my favorite I’ve had, and I’m a French roast lover. Everything was so perfectly balanced from the crisp almonds, slightly tart blueberries, and smooth syrup and banana, all on a crusted brioche bread. We finished it off by taking a freshly made chocolate chip cookie that was so good. Not a great picture admittedly, but it was soft and gooey without being doughy on the inside.  We thoroughly enjoyed this meal and it was made better by the sweet owner, good barista (who didn’t mind me chatting him up asking questions on how he made the drinks), and wonderful French music. The owner knows her business and obviously understands how busy people are in the financial district, but doesn’t rush you either. Favorite place we ate during our 4day trip!
